\subsection{RQ1: Effectiveness}
\label{sec:effectiveness}
On Java250 (Table~\ref{tab:java250_results}), all PLM$\rightarrow$GNN hybrids substantially outperform both GNN-only baselines and frozen PLM baselines. For example, the best hybrid configuration (GAT + StarCoder2-3B) reaches an F1 of 98.34\%, compared to 90.56\% for the best GNN-only model and 89.94\% for the best performing frozen PLM baseline. This pattern is consistent across all three PLMs; injecting PLM features into a GNN yields substantially higher performance than using either the PLM or the GNN in isolation.

